    comment: '<p>Basic operating system related utility functions are available through <strong>Node</strong>\'s <code>os</code> module.</p>\n<p>Firstly, the module must be imported:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">var os = require("os")\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get operating system name:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.type());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get operating system platform:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.platform());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get CPU\'s architecture (<code>x64</code>,<code>arm</code> or <code>ia32</code>):</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.arch());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get an array with various infrormation about the CPUs:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.cpus());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get the total system memory in bytes:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.totalmem());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Get an array with various information about all the Network Interfaces:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">console.log(os.networkInterfaces());\n</code></pre>\n',
